{"word":"τλητός","slug":"τλητός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τλητός</b></el> <el>(τλητός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a>of *<a href='S:τλάω'><el>τλάω</el></a>:\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>suffering, enduring, patient, steadfast</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, with a <a href='S:negativum'>negat.</a>, <el>οὐ τλ.</el> not <i>to be endured, intolerable</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}